@Watcher. He won’t necessarily be reviled by history. History is written by the victors; if Republicans succeed in installing permanent one party rule, he will be revered, with all the accompanying paraphernalia we see in other totalitarian countries: oversized photos and statues everywhere, required attendance and mandatory cheering at the military parades, his birthday, and yikes....all blonde anchors on Trump TV.

Of course, after having helped install him, most Republican legislators will be summarily dumped, now irrelevant and of no further use. 

I’m glad I lived during the pinnacle of American democracy. It’s depressing to watch it in danger of slipping away.

A Mickey Mouse song for this Mickey Mouse presidency:

Who's the leader of this land of Fox reality: D-O-N, A-L-D, T-R-U-M-P, Donald Trump (Hannity), Donald Trump (Hannity) the greatest con in U. S. history;

Who's the man who sold this land to Vlad and company: D-O-N, A-L-D, T-R-U-M-P, Donald Trump (Hannity), Donald Trump (Hannity),  much more worse than good old Hillary.

